@NODE Introducing "Introducing Convert"
@TOC Main

    @{b}Convert@{ub} converts text files between MAC/AMIGA/IBM. It only changes
the CR and LF's.

    To @{b}Convert@{ub} a file throw it's icon onto the Convert window or click
Convert and select the file in the appearing file requester.

    @{b}Convert@{ub} is fully font sensitive and is localized.

    Translation to french was done by myself and my french is not good, if you
make changes to the catalog, please send the corrected français.ct @{"to me" LINK Author}
too for including it into the next version.

@ENDNODE
@NODE Requirements "System Requirements"
@TOC Main

    @{b}Convert@{ub} should run on any Amiga system with at least 512K RAM and one
disk-drive. @{b}Convert@{ub} requires KickStart v2.04 or higher to run.

    @{b}Convert@{ub} also requires the ReqTools.library v38 or higher. ReqTools is
copyright 1993 by Nico François.

    Should you have any trouble running @{b}Convert@{ub} on your machine, please
@{"write to me" LINK Author} with the full specifications of your machine, that is KickStart
version, model, expansion boards etc...

@ENDNODE
@NODE Usage "How to use Convert"
@TOC Main
    @{b}Convert@{ub} can be started from the Shell or the Workbench.  

    CLI usage:

      Convert F=FROM/M,TO/K,S=SOURCE/K,D=DESTINATION/K,B=BUFFER=/K
      
        valid options for source are: A(MIGA) or M(AC) or I(BM) or ?(auto)

        valid options for destination are: A(MIGA) or M(AC) or I(BM)

        valid options for bufsize are: S(MALL) or M(EDIUM) or L(ARGE)
      
      If the source is a question mark Convert will try to find the type
      of file automatically by looking at the first occurrence of CR/LF.

      The keyword FROM is not needed when specifying which files must be converted. 
      if FROM files are omnitted the GUI window opens.

      The keyword TO specifies the target and can or must (multiple froms) be a
      directory, in that case the created file will have the same name as the
      FROM file and will be put in the TO directory.
      The TO keyword must be used when specifying the destination.

      If FROM and TO file are the same the file will be overwritten
      with the converted file.

    WB usage:

      Tooltypes:

        SOURCE      =   IBM | AMIGA | MAC | ?

        DESTINATION =   IBM | AMIGA | MAC

        BUFFER      =   SMALL | MEDIUM | LARGE

      If the SOURCE is a question mark Convert will try to find the type
      of file automatically by looking at the first occurrence of CR/LF.

      Method 1:
        Select Convert and shift double click the files to convert.
        Make sure the tooltypes of Convert are set correct!
        For every icon Convert asks a new name.

      Method 2:
        Double click Convert, a GUI window appears, set options
        (preset with tooltypes) and click the convert button or throw icons 
        on the window to Convert a file.

@ENDNODE
